gomodel:SYNGO_3114  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.12: \"Electron microscopic localization of a8 immunoreactivity in dendrites in the hilus of the dentate gyrus\"\n- \"B A higher-magnification micrograph of a dendritic spine showing a8 immunoreactivity associated with the post-synaptic density (arrow) and structures resembling the spine apparatus (arrowhead).\"\n\nFig.13: \"Ultrastructural localization of a8 labeling in dendrites in stratum radiatum of the CA3 region of the hippocampus\n- \"a8 immunoreactivity is shown in a dendritic shaft (D) primarily associated with a density post-synaptic to an unlabeled terminal (LIT). B: Labeling for a8 is found in a spine (arrow) emanating from the shaft of a small dendrite. A second dendritic spine on the same dendrite is apparently unlabeled (open arrow)\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Sprague-Dawley rats (Hilltop Lab. Animals, Inc.) were used in these experiments. \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3114" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
